Heat the oil in a saucepan and saut√© the onion and garlic for 2-3 minutes, to soften.Pour in the stock and bring to the boil. Add the mint and peas.  Reduce the heat and simmer gently for 8-10 minutes.Transfer the mixture to a liquidiser and blend until smooth.Return to the pan to warm through and add the cream, salt and freshly ground black pepper.Ladle into soup bowls to serve.